metadata.synopsis: A plain young woman (Patty Duke) gets an apartment in Greenwich Village, meets an artist (James Farentino) and acts kooky.

reviews: Director, Fred Coe, has the trick of making fearfully unpromising characters... more humanly bearable than the situation really warrants.
Me, Natalie is a pleasant film, very funny at times, and the evidence in the audience was that women liked it enormously.
